Create a new file in the People List project folder named app.js

A Basic Express Server
Open up the app.js file, and add the code for a simple web server.

Import the express and path modules, storing them in const variables
Create const variables for the hostname (127.0.0.1) and port (3000)
Initialize the by calling express() and storing the result in a variable named app
Define a new function named homePage with two parameters: request and response
In the body of the homePage function, use response.sendFile to send home.html
Use path.join to get the absolute path for home.html


Use app.get to specify that requests to the root ('/') should call the homePage callback
Define a function named listenCallback, and in the body, log the hostname and port
Finally, use app.listen to listen on the proper port and hostname, and pass listenCallback as the callback
