Store the database in a const named db


Define a function named connectCallback that takes an error parameter.
In the body of connectCallback, use throw to throw the error if there is one
In the body of connectCallback, log a message saying the database connection was successful
For testing purposes, in the body of connectCallback, send a SELECT query to the database, and log the results // test
 db.query('SELECT * FROM players', function (error, results) {
     console.log(results);
 });


