CRUD App - Read

Video

Follow the steps below to allow the web app to display data from the soccer database.
Getting the Homepage Data
Update the getHomePage function in the index.js file so that it pulls data from the database and renders it in the response.

Remove the current body of the getHomePage function
Create a new string variable named query that has SQL to find all players ordered by their id: SELECT * FROM players ORDER BY id ASC;


In the body of the getHomePage function, define a new function named queryCallback that takes error and result as parameters
Note, this is a function defined within another function!


In the body of the queryCallback function, check if error exists, and send a server error if it does: return response.status(500).send(error);


Beyond the if (error), create a new variable named renderData with a players property that has a value of result
